  "text": "We live in a turbulent world. Major changes are affecting societies and businesses in many countries, including the rapid pace of technological development, the continuing globalization of trade and the occurrence of major socio-economic and political changes in many parts of the world. Camarhina-Matos and Afsarmanesh (2005) identify the different types of collaborative networks that have emerged to address the economic, societal and scientific challenges in the contemporary world. Within the discipline of collaborative networks, supply networks are identified as goal-driven [CITATION_1] .",
